article_title: Australia to Withdraw Ambassador After Indonesia Executes ‘Bali Nine’ Prisoners
article_text:
CANBERRA, Australia—Australia will withdraw its ambassador to Indonesia and suspend high-level ministerial contact with its neighbor after the execution by Indonesia’s government of two Australians among eight drug convicts, Prime Minister Tony Abbott said Wednesday.

“This is a very important relationship between Australia and Indonesia. But it has suffered as a result of what’s been done,” Mr. Abbott told reporters in Canberra....
